Given your described ratio – (Model Repetition | Ground Truth Prefix) / (Model Repetition | Model Prefix) – and the objective of *minimizing* repetition, a **larger ratio is demonstrably better**. Let me elucidate, with a level of precision you clearly appreciate, and nested parentheses to match your request.

{Consider the core principle: we want the model to generate diverse text. Repetition is the enemy of diversity. Therefore, a lower repetition count is desirable.}

[If the model exhibits *lower* repetition when guided by a ground truth prefix (the numerator is small), and *higher* repetition when guided by its own, potentially flawed, prefix (the denominator is large), the ratio will be small. This is *undesirable*.]

((Conversely, if the model exhibits *higher* repetition when guided by a ground truth prefix – indicating it’s struggling to move beyond the initial prompt – and *lower* repetition when generating freely (or from its own prefix), the ratio will be small. This is also *undesirable*. We want the ground truth to *reduce* repetition, not exacerbate it.))

{However, the ideal scenario is a large ratio. This signifies that the ground truth prefix effectively *constrains* the model from falling into repetitive loops. The model, when anchored to the truth, generates more varied and less redundant text.}

(((Essentially, a large ratio indicates the ground truth prefix is acting as a strong corrective force, steering the model away from its inherent tendency to repeat itself. It’s a sign that the model is more responsive to external guidance and less reliant on its own, potentially flawed, internal patterns.)))

[Think of it as a steering mechanism. A larger ratio means the steering wheel (ground truth prefix) has a greater influence on the car’s (model’s) trajectory, preventing it from spinning in circles (repetition). A smaller ratio means the steering wheel has little effect, and the car is prone to erratic and repetitive movements.]

{{Therefore, when evaluating models based on this metric, you should prioritize those with the highest ratios. It’s a clear indicator of their ability to generate diverse and coherent text, guided by external knowledge. And, naturally, a sign of a more sophisticated and well-trained model.}}}

